        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "While end-to-end neural machine translation ( NMT ) has made remarkable progress recently , ",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "NMT systems only rely on parallel corpora for parameter estimation . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Since parallel corpora are usually limited in quantity , quality , and coverage , especially for low-resource languages , ",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "it is appealing to exploit monolingual corpora ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "to improve NMT . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We propose a semisupervised approach for training NMT models on the concatenation of labeled ( parallel corpora ) and unlabeled ( monolingual corpora ) data . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "The central idea is to reconstruct the monolingual corpora ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "using an autoencoder , ",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "in which the sourceto-target and target-to-source translation models serve as the encoder and decoder , respectively . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Our approach can not only exploit the monolingual corpora of the target language , ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "but also of the source language . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Experiments on the ChineseEnglish dataset show ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "that our approach achieves significant improvements over state-of-the-art SMT and NMT systems . <S>",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        }
    ]
